T1  - A Price Discrimination Analysis of Monetary Policy
PY  - 1984
Y1  - 1984/04/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297692
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 51
IS  - 2
SP  - 279
EP  - 288
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Monetary policy is analysed within a model that appeals to legal restrictions on private intermediation to explain the coexistence of currency and interest-bearing default-free bonds. The interaction between such legal restrictions and monetary policy is illustrated in a version of the overlapping generations model. The model shows that legal restrictions and the use of both currency and bonds permit the government to levy a nonlinear inflation tax and that such a tax may be better in terms of the Pareto criterion than a linear inflation tax.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297692
ER  - 



